latestPosts.caption:
I didn’t come from privilege.
No legacy. No godfather. No plan B.

Every day, I saw my dad work 12–14 hours non-stop.
No Sundays. No holidays.
Just one dream – that his son lives a better life.

So I chose CA.
Why? 
Because everyone said —
“CA ban gaya toh zindagi ban jaayegi.”

And honestly?
I failed.
Again. And again.
Friends moved ahead. Attempts kept increasing.
But I didn’t stop.

Eventually, I cracked it and entered corporate life.
Decent salary. Big office.
But slowly, I realised…
My dreams were shrinking.
My ambition was on mute.

Then COVID happened.
The world paused.
And for me – that pause became my turning point.

At night, I tried dropshipping.
By day, I worked full-time.
And slowly, I started teaching students as a side hustle.

People laughed —
“Teaching? Seriously?”
But something in me whispered:

“Try once. Just once. What if this works?”

One day, I made the boldest decision of my life —
I QUIT CORPORATE.

Everyone said I was stupid.
But deep inside, a voice said:
"apni hi kahani hai, ending change karlenge.”

Today?
I’m that guy people call “lucky”.
But they don’t see the sleepless nights,
the silent tears,
the endless self-doubt.

So if you’re stuck in the middle of your story…
If life feels off-track…

Just remember:

It’s YOUR story.
You still hold the pen.
You can change the ending.

Peace.

MISTAKE IN FORECASTING

Why 90% Forecasts Go Wrong

Business forecasting is not about Excel tricks.
It’s about clear thinking.

Most people fail because of Anchoring Bias —

Once a number is in your head, you start building stories around it.

Instead, ask better questions:
 ✔️ Is the business efficient?
 ✔️ Does it survive downturns?
 ✔️ How strong is the moat?

A good forecast isn’t a guess — it’s a conclusion from real insights.
